<note id="fs-id1167064626583" class="learning-objectives"><label/><title>Section Learning Objectives</title>
<para id="fs-id1167066025057">By the end of this section, you will be able to do the following:</para>
<list id="fs-id1167063208255">
<item>Describe and predict image formation and magnification as a consequence of refraction through convex and concave lenses, use ray diagrams to confirm image formation, and discuss how these properties of lenses determine their applications</item>
<item>Explain how the human eye works in terms of geometric optics</item>
<item>Perform calculations, based on the thin-lens equation, to determine image and object distances, focal length, and image magnification, and use these calculations to confirm values determined from ray diagrams</item>
</list>
</note>
