<para id="fs-id1167065870878">The examples in <link target-id="Figure_16_03_ConvexL2"/> and <link target-id="Figure_16_03_Concave_Convex"/> represent the three possible cases—case 1, case 2, and case 3—summarized in <link target-id="Table_16_03"/>. In the table, <emphasis effect="italics">m</emphasis> is magnification; the other symbols have the same meaning as they did for curved mirrors.</para>

